    question: 'Is it normal for one armpit to smell more than the other?',
    answer: 'Yes. Asymmetrical body odor is common during puberty as sweat glands mature at slightly different rates. It can also be influenced by which arm is dominant or differences in hygiene (missing a spot while washing). It is rarely a medical concern. Encourage thorough washing of both underarms with a mild soap during the daily shower.'
